cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the construction and analysis of a geometric graph, specifically a greedy spanner, for a set of points in the Euclidean plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The analysis involves bounding the number of edge crossings, which is a combinatorial problem and relates to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of spanners to approximate pairwise distances is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and the construction of separator hierarchies is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
